Backnd Form and Data Storage

Objective
Create an HTML form, send data to backend using Flask, store data in SQLite database, and display stored records.

Technologies Used
Python
Flask
SQLite3
HTML

Steps Performed
Installed Flask framework
Created HTML student registration form
Connected Flask backend with SQLite database
Accepted user input from form
Stored student data in database
Fetched and displayed stored records on webpage

Files Included
app.py – Flask backend application
database.db – SQLite database file
templates/index.html – Student form page
templates/students.html – Display stored data page

Output
Student details entered through the form are successfully stored in the database and displayed on the browser.

Result
Backend form submission and database storage implemented successfully using Flask and SQLite.